cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NA, cs.OH 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with image reconstruction and material characterization using CT scans, which falls under the purview of computer vision. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a model-based iterative approach to solve the problem of stabilizing dual-energy CT reconstructions, which involves information theory concepts such as regularization and optimization. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with processing and analysis of multi-energy CT scans, which can be considered a form of multimedia data. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a numerical method (alternating direction method of multipliers) to solve the problem of stabilizing dual-energy CT reconstructions, which falls under the purview of numerical analysis. 
- cs.OH (Other Computer Science): This paper could also be classified under the "Other Computer Science" category, as it deals with a specific application of CT scans and does not fit neatly into any one sub-category.
